OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Fri 6 Mar to Sun 15 Mar
OL,6,FHigh pressure looks to hold the
OL,7,Fgreatest influence for much of this
OL,8,Fperiod, especially towards the south
OL,9,For southeast of the UK. This means
OL,10,Fthat many places will see plenty of
OL,11,Fdry weather with variable cloud
OL,12,Famounts and some sunshine. The best of
OL,13,Fthe sunny weather is most likely
OL,14,Ftowards the south or southeast. Some
OL,15,Fovernight fog is possible given clear
OL,16,Fskies and light winds. However,
OL,17,Ffrontal systems are still likely to
OL,18,Faffect the north and west of the UK at
OL,19,Ftimes, perhaps pushing further east on
OL,20,Foccasion, bringing some rain and
OL,21,Fstrong winds, and perhaps some hill
OL,22,Fsnow across high ground in the north.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,FTemperatures will be near or above
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fnormal, although a few patchy
OL,25,Fovernight frosts are still likely.
